section.section:
"Exposure" means:
Percutaneous contact with blood or body fluids;
Mucocutaneous contact with blood or body fluids;
Open wound, including dermatitis, exudative lesions, or chapped skin, contact with blood or body fluids for a prolonged period; or
Intact skin contact with large amounts of blood or body fluids for a prolonged period.

"Public safety worker" means:
A career or volunteer member of a fire, rescue, or emergency medical services department, company, squad, or auxiliary;
A law enforcement officer;
The State Fire Marshal or a sworn member of the State Fire Marshal's office; or
A forensic scientist who works under the direction of a law enforcement agency.
